        <!-- ARTICLE 1 -->
        <article id="about">
            <h3>About MinecraftCon</h3>

            <p>
                <b>MinecraftCon</b> is an annual convention celebrating the game 
                <cite>Minecraft</cite> and its creative community. Fans gather to explore
                <mark>mods</mark>, <mark>redstone</mark>, and <mark>survival strategies</mark>.
            </p>

            <p>
                The convention focuses on creativity, collaboration, and learning.
                Whether you enjoy building, coding, or storytelling, there is something
                for everyone.
            </p>

            <blockquote>
                “In Minecraft, every block is a new possibility.”
            </blockquote>

            <p>
                <abbr title="Player versus Player">PvP</abbr> tournaments and
                <abbr title="Player versus Environment">PvE</abbr> challenges will be featured.
            </p>
        </article>

        <!-- ARTICLE 2 -->
        <article id="schedule">
            <h3>Event Schedule</h3>

            <p>
                The convention runs from 
                <time datetime="2026-06-12">June 12, 2026</time> to 
                <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>.
            </p>

            <pre>
Day 1: Keynotes and Panels
Day 2: Workshops and Competitions
Day 3: Community Builds and Closing Ceremony
            </pre>

            <p>
                Attendees will learn how commands like 
                <code>/give</code> and <code>/fill</code> can transform gameplay.
            </p>

            <q>Minecraft teaches problem-solving through play.</q>
        </article>

        <!-- ARTICLE 3 -->
        <article id="guests">
            <h3>Featured Guests</h3>

            <p>
                Meet popular creators, developers, and educators from the Minecraft
                community. Special panels will discuss game design and creativity.
            </p>

            <p>
                Some sessions will explore <i>ethical building</i> in multiplayer servers
                and <u>fair gameplay</u> practices.
            </p>
        </article>

        <!-- SECTION -->
        <section id="location">
            <h3>Location</h3>

            <p>
                MinecraftCon 2026 will be hosted in Austin, Texas, offering a modern
                venue with space for exhibits, tournaments, and workshops.
            </p>
        </section>

